HEADWORD: Durative
<hw>Dur"a*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Continuing; not
completed; implying duration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Its <qex>durative</qex> tense, which expresses the thought of it
as going on.</q> <rj><qau>J. Byrne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

